p: The MIC analyses showed that 100% of the strains were resistant to 5 products (OA1, OA2, OA3, OA5 and OA8) up to 3500 μg mL -1 of each product ( Table 5), and 15, 25 and 10% of the strains were sensitive to OA4, OA6 and OA7, respectively, at concentrations equal to or lower than 1500 μg mL -1 ( Table 5). In general, most of the strains showed sensitivity to product (OA9, Table 5). Product EO1 controlled 100% of the strains between 100 to 3000 μg mL -1. Forty percent of the strains (8/20) were sensitive up to 3000 μg mL -1 against EO2 ( Table 5).
